        <!-- About Content Starts -->
          <div class="page-box">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-sm-8">
                <h3>Cooking</h3>
                <h4></h4>
                <p>
                  Once you sign up as a cook you can start offering meals. We highly recommend to upload a high quality image of your meal.
									At the moment you can only upload one image. Here are a few important things to keep in mind when going through the new meal process:
									<ul>
										<li>You must specify a meal availability time range. This is the time when the customer can expect to have the meal delivered to them or pick up.</li>
										<li>You must either deliver your meal for free or have the customer pick it up at the time the customer specifies during the ordering process</li>
										<li>You are resposible providing the meals in the proper containers.</li>
										<li>You will have an option to de-activate a meal and it will no longer show up on our site.</li>
										<li>You will always have access to the created meal data and can therefore offer it again in the future if desired.</li>
										<li>Your email address will be made available to the customer when they place an order in case the customer has any questions.</li>
										<li>Please keep in mind that you will paid the meal price you set MINUS a CookedNearby.Com fee of 22%. E.g. A meal offered at $11.99 will be paid out as $9.35.</li>
										<li>Please allow a 15 minute grace period when offering your meals. E.g. a meal offered from 4 PM to 7 PM can be picked up or delivered as early as 3:45 PM. or as late 7:15PM.</li>
										<li>Only deliver freshly cooked meals to your customers. Keep your food warm but not for longer than one hour.</li>
										<li>Don't forget to share your meals on instagram and facebook to let your friends know you are cooking.</li>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <br />
            <p>
            </p>
